        <p><strong>Windows Vista</strong> (codenamed "<strong><em>Longhorn</em></strong>"), is an operating system by <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft', 'C'); ?> for use on personal computers.</p>
        <p>The release of Windows Vista came more than five years after the introduction of its predecessor, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows XP', 'WIN'); ?>, the longest time span between successive releases of <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft Windows', 'OS'); ?> desktop operating systems.</p>
        <p>New features of Windows Vista include an updated graphical user interface and visual style dubbed <strong>Aero</strong>, a new search component called <strong>Windows Search</strong>, redesigned networking, audio, print and display sub-systems, and new multimedia tools including <strong>Windows DVD Maker</strong>.</p>
